  "rationale": "<p>Sine and cosine of complementary angles are equal: since 35\u00b0 + 55\u00b0 = 90\u00b0, we have cos 55\u00b0 = sin 35\u00b0 and sin 55\u00b0 = cos 35\u00b0. Substituting into the given expression: sin 35\u00b0 \u00b7 sin 35\u00b0 + cos 35\u00b0 \u00b7 cos 35\u00b0 = (sin 35\u00b0)\u00b2 + (cos 35\u00b0)\u00b2 = (cos 55\u00b0)\u00b2 + (cos 35\u00b0)\u00b2 = 1.</p>",
